did.unittitle: University of Kentucky. Special Collections Research Center. General Reference Subject files
did.abstract: The University of Kentucky Libraries. Special Collections Research Center. University Archives general reference subject files (dated 1865-2019; 93.04 cubic feet 22 Megabytes, 259 document boxes, 13 slim document boxes, 10 files) comprise vertical files of primarily newspaper clippings, press releases, and printed material on subjects, names, and locations relating to University of Kentucky research, teaching, service, health care, students, faculty, staff, administration, colleges, centers, departments, history, events, and activities.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open to researchers by appointment

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Collection is arranged chronologically into four series: Administrative and General, 1865-1955; General and Administrative files, 1956-1963; Administrative and General, 1963-2001 June 30; General, 2001 July 1-2019

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The University of Kentucky is the flagship, land-grant university for the Commonwealth of Kentucky located in Lexington, Kentucky. It was established by an Act of the Legislature in 1865 as the Agricultural and Mechanical College of Kentucky University (now Transylvania University). In 1878, the Legislature split A&M College from Kentucky University, and it became State College and began developing into a university. In 1908, the Legislature changed the name from State College to State University. In 1916, the Legislature again changed the name from State University to University of Kentucky.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: 2018ua018 : [identification of item], University of Kentucky. Special Collections Research Center general reference subject files, 1865-2019, University of Kentucky Special Collections Research Center.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The University of Kentucky Libraries. Special Collections Research Center. University Archives general reference subject files (dated 1865-2019; 93.04 cubic feet 22 Megabytes, 259 document boxes, 13 slim document boxes, 10 files) comprise vertical files of primarily newspaper clippings, press releases, and printed material on subjects, names, and locations relating to University of Kentucky research, teaching, service, health care, students, faculty, staff, administration, colleges, centers, departments, history, events, and activities. The general reference subject files were created by University of Kentucky librarians and archivists.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Property rights reside with the University of Kentucky. The University of Kentucky holds the copyright for materials created in the course of business by University of Kentucky employees. Copyright for all other materials has not been assigned to the University of Kentucky. For information about permission to reproduce or publish, please contact the Special Collections Research Center.
